cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for training convolutional neural networks to rely more on global structures of the image rather than local patterns. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the generalization of the networks, which is a common goal in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions benchmark domain adaptation tasks, which suggests that it may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset, which may indicate that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
